\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces HCCP at a glance. \textbf  {(a)} Per-cell empirical coverage on TraitGym Complex (CADD+GPN-MSA+Borzoi, $\pi _{+}{=}0.10$, $K{=}5$): three coverage grids over $Y \times \hat  {\sigma }$-bin, colored by deviation from $1{-}\alpha {=}0.90$ (red = under, blue = over). \textbf  {(i)} Split CP collapses on both ends of $\hat  {\sigma }$ (worst cell $0.67$). \textbf  {(ii)} class-Mondrian \citep  {sadinle2019lac} fixes the class budget but leaves $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin variation within each class unconstrained (worst cell $0.80$). \textbf  {(iii)} HCCP partitions on $Y \times \hat  {\sigma }$-bin and holds every cell within $\pm 0.04$ of target. The nonconformity score $s(x,y) = |y - \hat  {p}(x)| / (\hat  {\sigma }(x) + \epsilon )$ with per-cell calibration restores both (T2) class- and (T3) bin-conditional coverage, compatible with \citet  {barber2020limits}'s pointwise impossibility. \textbf  {(b)} Pareto plot on (Cov$|Y{=}1$, $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin gap) using Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:h2h} bootstrap means ($B{=}200$). HCCP is the only method in the ideal corner (cov $\geq 0.85$, gap $\leq 0.20$) on both datasets; B1, B2, B3 each fail at least one axis at $\pi _{+}{=}0.10$.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:concept}{{1}{2}{HCCP at a glance. \textbf {(a)} Per-cell empirical coverage on TraitGym Complex (CADD+GPN-MSA+Borzoi, $\pi _{+}{=}0.10$, $K{=}5$): three coverage grids over $Y \times \shat $-bin, colored by deviation from $1{-}\alpha {=}0.90$ (red = under, blue = over). \textbf {(i)} Split CP collapses on both ends of $\shat $ (worst cell $0.67$). \textbf {(ii)} class-Mondrian \citep {sadinle2019lac} fixes the class budget but leaves $\shat $-bin variation within each class unconstrained (worst cell $0.80$). \textbf {(iii)} HCCP partitions on $Y \times \shat $-bin and holds every cell within $\pm 0.04$ of target. The nonconformity score $s(x,y) = |y - \phat (x)| / (\shat (x) + \epsilon )$ with per-cell calibration restores both (T2) class- and (T3) bin-conditional coverage, compatible with \citet {barber2020limits}'s pointwise impossibility. \textbf {(b)} Pareto plot on (Cov$|Y{=}1$, $\shat $-bin gap) using Tab.~\ref {tab:h2h} bootstrap means ($B{=}200$). HCCP is the only method in the ideal corner (cov $\geq 0.85$, gap $\leq 0.20$) on both datasets; B1, B2, B3 each fail at least one axis at $\pi _{+}{=}0.10$}{figure.1}{}}
