\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {20}{\ignorespaces $K$-sweep on Mendelian and Complex (CADD+GPN-MSA+Borzoi, $\alpha = 0.10$, single seed, legacy non-nested K-selection). Worst-cell gap = $\qopname  \relax m{max}_{k,b} |\mathrm  {cov}_{k,b} - 0.90|$ on the test fold; $n_{\qopname  \relax m{min}}$ = minimum calibration count per cell; fallback = cells triggering pooled backoff. Bolded rows are the legacy minimum (test-fold leakage; superseded by nested-CV $\hat  K(c_{\mathrm  {outer}})$ in §\ref  {sec:theory:t5} and Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:LF_estimators}). Single-seed values here are smaller than the bootstrap means in Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:cp_baselines} because they ride the favourable test fold the legacy selector tunes against.}}{30}{table.20}\protected@file@percent }
